definition.value: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which both the acyl groups are specified as (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl.
A beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1)-ceramide in which the ceramide component is specified as N-acylsphinganine.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as palmitoyl and linoleoyl respectively.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-) in which the 1- and 2-acyl substituent are specified as palmitoyl and (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl respectively; major species at pH 7.3.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which both acyl groups are specified as palmitoyl (hexadecanoyl).

An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and carboxy functions as well as protonation of the amino function of 3-(3-amino-3-carboxypropyl)uridine 5'-phosphate residue; major species at 7.3.
An  aryl sulfate that is 4-hydroxystyrene in which the hydroxy group has been replaced by a sulfooxy group.
An aryl sulfate that is 4-ethylphenol in which the hydroxy group has been replaced by a sulfooxy group.
Metabolites produced by the gut microbiota or microorganisms (e.g. bacteria and fungi) that live in the digestive tracts of animals.
A glucosylceramide consisting of a beta-D-glucosyl residue attached to the primary hydroxyl group of N-acyl-(4E,8E)-9-methylsphinga-4,8-dienine.
An aryl sulfate that is ethylbenzene substituted by a sulfooxy group at position 3.
A galactosylceramide consisting of a beta-D-galactosyl residue attached to the primary hydroxyl group of N-acyl-(4E,8E)-9-methylsphinga-4,8-dienine.
A member of the class of thiazolidenediones that is the hydroxy derivative of pioglitazone.

An anionic ganglioside  arising from deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy groups of beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->4)-[alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->8)-alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->3)]-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1')-ceramide; major species at pH 7.3.

An anionic ganglioside arising from deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy groups of alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->4)-[alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->8)-alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->3)]-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1')-ceramide; major species at pH 7.3.

A sulfonamide with a structure based on that of sulfanilamide substituted on the sulfonamide nitrogen by a (2R,3S)-4-phenyl-2-(phosphonooxy)-3-({[(3S)-tetrahydrofuran-3-yloxy]carbonyl}amino)butyl group. It is a pro-drug of the HIV protease inhibitor and antiretroviral drug amprenavir.
An aryl sulfate that is the 3-hydroxy derivative of  paracetamol sulfate.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine where the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are palmitoyl and icosanoyl respectively.
A member of the class of acetamides that is paracetamol sulfate substituted by a methoxy group at position 3.

An anionic ganglioside arising from deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy groups of N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->4)-[alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->3)]-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->4)-[alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->3)]-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1')-ceramide; major species at pH 7.3.
A fatty acid ester obtained by the formal condensation of the hydroxy group of butan-1-ol with the carboxy group of oleic acid.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3-phosphate in which both phosphatidyl acyl groups are specified as octanoyl.
A phosphatidylinositol 3-phosphate in which both phosphatidyl acyl groups are specified as palmitoyl (hexadecanoyl)
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as palmitoyl and (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl respectively.

An anionic ganglioside that is the conjugate base of N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->4)-[alpha-N-glycoloylneuraminosyl-(2->3)]-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1')-ceramide arising from deprotonation of the glycoloylneuraminosyl carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

An anionic ganglioside that is the conjugate base of alpha-N-glycoloylneuraminosyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1')-ceramide arising from deprotonation of the glycoloylneuraminosyl carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An O-acyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group is specified as glutaroyl.
An organosulfate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the sulfate group of any 1-(3-O-sulfo-beta-D-galactosyl)-ceramide; major species at pH 7.3.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,5-bisphosphate in which both phosphatidyl acyl groups are specified as palmitoyl (hexadecanoyl).
A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 2-(hydroxymethyl)butanoic acid.
A branched-chain saturated fatty acid that is butanoic acid substituted by a hydroxymethyl group at position 2. It is a metabolite derived from the isoleucine metabolism.
A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3-hydroxyisovaleric acid.
A ceramide 1-phosphate(2-) in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as hexanoyl; major species at pH 7.3.

A pyrimidone that is pyrimidin-4(3H)-one in which the hydrogens at positions 2, 3, 5 and 6 are replaced by 2-[(5-methyl-1,3,4-oxadiazole-2-carbonyl)amino]propan-2-yl, methyl, hydroxy, and N-[(4-fluorophenyl)methyl]aminoacyl groups, respectively. It is an antiretroviral drug used for treatment of HIV infection.
A monocarboxylic acid anion resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group of 17beta-estradiol 17-glucosiduronic acid.
An organic sodium salt that has 17beta-estradiol 17-glucosiduronate as the anion.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3-phosphate in which both phosphatidyl acyl groups are specified as palmitoyl (hexadecanoyl).
A dipeptide composed of L-glutamic acid and L-methionine joined by a peptide linkage.
A dipeptide composed of glutamic acid and phenylalanine joined together by a peptide linkage.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (11Z)-3-oxohexadecenoic acid.
A dipeptide composed of glutamic acid and  threonine joined by a peptide linkage.
A dipeptide composed of L-glutamic acid and L-tyrosine joined by a peptide linkage.
A polyketide obtained by hydrolysis of the pyranone ring of dihydromonacolin L.
A polyketide obtained by hydrolysis of the pyranone ring of monacolin J.
A polyketide obtainbed by allylic hydroxylation of dihydromonacolin L acid at the 3alpha-position.
An EC 3.4.24.* (metalloendopeptidase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of neprilysin (EC 3.4.24.11).
An EC 3.4.24.* (metalloendopeptidase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of endothelin-converting enzyme 1 (EC 3.4.24.71).
